There’s also a lot of tiny little bakeries all along the street that sell all sorts of bread and pastries.

Which Foods Do The Locals Eat?

The foods they eat in Iran are very similar to the ones that we have in the United States.

Fish and rice is what they eat the most, along with lots of cheeses. They also have something called “Shir Kebab” which is basically sliced almonds.

Be aware that as a single traveler, it’s not very common to find other singles in a hotel room in Tehran (unless you’re a girl).

Most solo guests are over there to teach English or study with private tutors.

They don’t plan to go out and party, drink heavily or have “coffee with strangers” as a national pastime.

I’ve heard of a few foreigners getting into trouble with the police there but none of these things ever happened to me or my other “type-A” girlfriends who stayed in the city for years.

If you want to do some sightseeing around Tehran alone in your hotel room, I wouldn’t make too big a deal about it.

I’ve found that Iranians are really adaptive and accept a wide range of social norms.

You can even get fined if you’re caught drinking alcohol in Iran: https://www.deviantart.com/musiccreate3211/art/Iran-Tehran
